# Mobius Chat — Cloud Run deployment config for mobius-os-dev.
#
# This file is the single source of truth for NON-SECRET runtime
# config when deploying to the mobius-os-dev project. Secrets (API
# keys, JWT_SECRET, DB password) come from GCP Secret Manager and are
# wired up in scripts/deploy.sh via --set-secrets, not from here.
#
# Rules
# -----
# * Plain KEY=value, one per line. No ``export``, no shell
#   interpolation — this file is sourced by scripts/deploy.sh and fed
#   verbatim into ``gcloud run deploy --set-env-vars=...``.
# * Commit this file. It must never contain secrets.
# * Adding a new env var: add here, document why inline, and reference
#   it in deploy/README.md if it changes rollout behavior.
# * A prod equivalent (deploy/prod.env) will fork off this file once
#   the beta proves out on dev.

# ── GCP project + region ────────────────────────────────────────────
# These two drive ``gcloud`` flag defaults in deploy.sh. Separate from
# the runtime env below because they're ``gcloud`` inputs, not Cloud
# Run container env.
GCP_PROJECT=mobius-os-dev
GCP_REGION=us-central1

# ── Cloud Run service identity ──────────────────────────────────────
SERVICE_NAME=mobius-chat
SERVICE_ACCOUNT=mobius-platform-dev@mobius-os-dev.iam.gserviceaccount.com
# Artifact Registry repo (scripts/bootstrap_gcp.sh creates this on
# first run if missing). Image tag is appended by deploy.sh using
# the current git SHA.
AR_REPO=mobius-chat
IMAGE_BASE=us-central1-docker.pkg.dev/mobius-os-dev/mobius-chat/chat

# ── Cloud SQL ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Instance connection name is the Cloud SQL Proxy target. Chat talks
# to Postgres via the /cloudsql Unix socket mounted by Cloud Run when
# --add-cloudsql-instances is passed.
CLOUDSQL_INSTANCE=mobius-os-dev:us-central1:mobius-platform-dev-db
CLOUDSQL_DATABASE=mobius_chat
# IAM db user: the Cloud SQL database user that authenticates via the
# service account's GCP identity — no password needed, the Cloud SQL
# Proxy + IAM auth handle credentials. Must equal the service account
# email (SQL escapes the @ automatically on connection).
CLOUDSQL_IAM_USER=mobius-platform-dev@mobius-os-dev.iam

# ── Runtime env (passed to container via --set-env-vars) ─────────────
# Strict environment mode — enforces the fallback-gate checks in
# app/config.py (rejects localhost URLs for task-manager/skills-mcp,
# requires /cloudsql socket in DATABASE_URL, etc.).
CHAT_ENV=prod
CHAT_ENV_STRICT=1
MOBIUS_PROD=1

# Queue type. 2026-04-27: switched memory → redis when min-instances
# went from 1 → 4. The in-process MemoryQueue is per-instance, so
# multi-instance breaks polling (POSTs land on A, GETs round-robin
# to B/C/D and see "pending" because B/C/D have no record). Redis
# gives shared queue + response store across all instances.
# Memorystore is reached via the VPC connector (see RUN_VPC_CONNECTOR).
CHAT_QUEUE_TYPE=redis
REDIS_URL=redis://10.40.102.67:6379/0

# DB mode. ``direct`` bypasses mobius-db-agent (not deployed in the
# monolith beta) and goes straight to Cloud SQL via psycopg2.
# Remove this line once db-agent is deployed — default behavior is
# MCP-first with psycopg2 fallback on connection error.
CHAT_DB_MODE=direct

# Per-request wall-clock ceiling. 90s matches P99 of real turns with
# an LLM retry. Cloud Run's service timeout below is 300s so this
# fires first and publishes a graceful turn_failed response.
# 180s (not 90s) because beta traffic exercises web_scrape +
# multi-round ReAct which legitimately runs past the P99 of
# corpus-only turns. Background-thread deadline path (monolith)
# uses this same value.
MOBIUS_TURN_DEADLINE_S=300

# Request body cap. /upload and /chat/roster-upload are exempt (they
# legitimately ship megabytes of document content).
CHAT_MAX_REQUEST_BYTES=1048576

# Vertex AI project. MUST equal GCP_PROJECT above for IAM to resolve;
# assert_hosted_config refuses to boot if this is the "mobiusos-new"
# placeholder.
VERTEX_PROJECT_ID=mobius-os-dev

# Cloud SQL connection string. 2026-04-20 beta: using the built-in
# ``postgres`` superuser + password (injected from Secret Manager as
# CHAT_DB_PASSWORD) because Cloud SQL IAM auth requires the Python
# connector library (extra dep + more moving parts). The URL here
# carries NO password — app/db_client._get_fallback_url injects
# CHAT_DB_PASSWORD at connect time. When we split off db-agent and
# add cloud-sql-python-connector, swap back to the IAM user:
#   postgresql+psycopg2://mobius-platform-dev%40mobius-os-dev.iam@/mobius_chat?host=/cloudsql/...
# CHAT_RAG_DATABASE_URL — chat's primary DB.
# Holds chat_state, threads, turns, etc. Chat WRITES to this DB.
# Original architecture: mobius_rag (ingestion) → DBT clone → BigQuery
# → DBT → mobius_chat (what chat reads). The DBT path is skipped for
# beta; corpus tables were supposed to be published via
# scripts/publish_corpus_to_chat.sh.
CHAT_RAG_DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg2://postgres@/mobius_chat?host=/cloudsql/mobius-os-dev:us-central1:mobius-platform-dev-db

# CORPUS_RAG_DATABASE_URL — read-only handle on mobius_rag for the
# BM25 retrieval arm + the JPD tagger / doc-authority lookups in the
# reranker. After pgvector cutover the chat-side copy of the corpus
# (in mobius_chat) stopped being maintained; mobius-retriever's BM25
# was hitting empty/stale tables and returning 0 chunks every turn,
# making "hybrid" effectively single-arm. Pointing the read path
# directly at mobius_rag restores the second arm without touching
# the write path (chat_state etc. still goes to mobius_chat).
#
# Trade-off: tight read coupling chat → rag DB. Acceptable for beta;
# the corpus_search skill extraction in mobius-rag retires this URL
# entirely (BM25 will run server-side, chat just consumes via HTTP).
CORPUS_RAG_DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg2://postgres@/mobius_rag?host=/cloudsql/mobius-os-dev:us-central1:mobius-platform-dev-db

# Task-manager + skills-mcp URLs. Neither is deployed yet for the
# beta, so we use sentinels that the startup gate will accept
# (non-localhost) while the features are turned OFF below. When
# task-manager deploys, replace these with the real Cloud Run URL.
CHAT_SKILLS_TASK_MANAGER_URL=https://task-manager.not-yet-deployed.invalid
# MCP tool server — provider-roster-credentialing now mounts FastMCP at /mcp
# on the same Cloud Run port (8010) as the REST API. Points here so chat's
# startup probe can auto-register all 16 FL Medicaid data tools.
CHAT_SKILLS_MCP_URL=https://mobius-provider-roster-credentialing-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app/mcp

# Mobius-skills microservices — deployed to Cloud Run 2026-04-21.
# All reuse the mobius-platform-dev SA + Cloud SQL socket + shared
# Chroma (34.170.243.161). Runs on mobius-os-dev.
CHAT_SKILLS_DOC_READER_URL=https://mobius-doc-reader-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app
WEB_SCRAPER_URL=https://mobius-web-scraper-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app/scrape/review
GOOGLE_SEARCH_URL=https://mobius-google-search-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app/search
CHAT_SKILLS_HEALTHCARE_URL=https://mobius-healthcare-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app
CHAT_SKILLS_INSTANT_RAG_URL=https://mobius-instant-rag-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app
# CHAT_SKILLS_EMAIL_URL — chat's email skill (preview→send) target.
# Was being set out-of-band via ``gcloud run services update`` and got
# wiped by every redeploy because it wasn't baked here. Anchored in
# dev.env 2026-05-06 to make redeploys idempotent. mobius-email runs on
# the shared mobius-platform-dev SA; reachable from chat over the VPC
# connector (same egress path as the other skills).
CHAT_SKILLS_EMAIL_URL=https://mobius-email-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app
# MOBIUS_RAG_URL (2026-04-27 consolidation) — chat document uploads
# now POST raw multipart to {MOBIUS_RAG_URL}/upload?ttl_days=7&...
# instead of going through the instant-rag skill. Same host as
# RAG_API_BASE; kept as a separate name so a future read/write split
# can flip just this one env without affecting the curator/retrieval
# paths.
MOBIUS_RAG_URL=https://mobius-rag-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app
# MOBIUS_RAG_UI_URL (2026-04-29) — base URL for the rag UI's upload
# tab. Used by the chat upload handler's "redirect" UX path: when the
# user uploads a >10-min document, chat returns a redirect_url pointing
# here with ?prefill=true&filename=<name> so the user can complete the
# upload in the rag UI instead of locking the conversation. Defaults
# to MOBIUS_RAG_URL when unset (rag API and UI share a host today).
MOBIUS_RAG_UI_URL=https://mobius-rag-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app
# mobius-vibe service (2026-04-24): generates short, work-adjacent
# vibe lines (toasts, empathy, dry observations, gratitude) when the
# planner picks the ``vibe`` builtin skill. Service URL must end in
# /vibe — the skill posts directly to that path. Default in code is
# localhost:8050/vibe; we override to the deployed Cloud Run URL.
CHAT_SKILLS_VIBE_URL=https://mobius-vibe-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app/vibe
# fetch_document skill (2026-04-25): resolves a corpus document by
# name/policy-ID and returns mobius-rag's /documents/{id}/download/pdf
# URL. Same host as RAG_APP_BASE today (the doc-reader iframe target).
RAG_API_BASE=https://mobius-rag-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app
# RAG_API_URL — separate from RAG_API_BASE because the curator tools
# (lookup_authoritative_sources / ingest_url, Phase 13.5) read this
# specific name and the existing retrieval API path (retriever_backend,
# non_patient_rag) keys off it too. Same host today; kept distinct so
# we can route admin/write ops to a different endpoint later if we
# split the read/write surfaces.
RAG_API_URL=https://mobius-rag-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app

# OS_API_URL — mobius-os gateway URL. The corpus_search skill (chat
# side, app/skills/builtin/corpus_search.py) POSTs to
# {OS_API_URL}/api/v1/skills/corpus_search with header X-Caller=chat.
# mobius-os proxies to mobius-rag, attaches caller attribution, and
# logs each call to search_events.caller. When mobius-os goes live
# replace the placeholder; until then the skill returns a clean
# no_sources envelope with diagnostic in extra.error="os_api_url_unset".
OS_API_URL=https://mobius-os.not-yet-deployed.invalid

# ── ChromaDB (shared vector store) ──────────────────────────────
# GCE e2-micro ``mobius-chroma`` in us-central1-a, port 8000, token
# auth via X-Chroma-Token header. Same target used by local dev so
# there's exactly one index to debug. When we migrate to pgvector,
# remove these three and the HttpClient path becomes dead code.
CHROMA_HOST=34.170.243.161
CHROMA_PORT=8000
CHROMA_SSL=0
CHROMA_COLLECTION=published_rag
# Tells the new dispatch logic (chat_config.vector_store) to route
# retrieval through the ChromaDB backend rather than Vertex Vector
# Search. Without this the published_rag_search fallback could choose
# Vertex even though the CHROMA_* vars are set.
CHAT_VECTOR_STORE=chroma

# Disable task-manager promotion for the beta — it's default-ON in
# code (2026-04-20 flip) but without a real endpoint the fire-and-
# forget POSTs would log warnings every turn. Re-enable by deleting
# this line once task-manager is deployed.
MOBIUS_TASK_MANAGER_PROMOTION=0

# CORS. Chicken-and-egg: strict CORS gate requires a value at boot,
# but the Cloud Run *.run.app URL only exists after the first deploy.
# Seed with ``*`` so the service comes up, then tighten to the real
# service URL after the first deploy:
#
#   1. scripts/deploy.sh dev  (boots with *)
#   2. Grab the printed service URL
#   3. Set CHAT_CORS_ORIGINS=<url> here + commit
#   4. scripts/deploy.sh dev --skip-build   (reapplies with real origin)
#
# This is safe for beta because there's no auth + no write endpoints
# that would care about cross-origin abuse at this stage. Tighten
# before wiring MOBIUS_OS_AUTH_URL.
CHAT_CORS_ORIGINS=https://mobius-chat-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app,https://mobius-story-ui-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app

# Auth (2026-04-23, Sprint 1 #5): shift to 'optional' to start honoring
# JWTs when clients send them — lets L3 rate limiting activate for
# authed traffic and exercises the auth path — while keeping
# unauthenticated requests working until every client adopts the token
# flow. Flip to 'required' when clients are all sending tokens.
#
# MOBIUS_OS_AUTH_URL: chat now CALLS this URL via the auth_proxy router
# (app/api/auth_proxy.py — 2026-05-06). Forwards /api/v1/auth/{path:path}
# and /api/v1/public-config to mobius-user, the canonical identity +
# preferences service. Frontend's @mobius/auth modal stays bound to
# window.origin/api/v1, so the browser sees same-origin only — no CORS
# config needed on mobius-user for chat callers.
#
# Spec: Mobius-user/SPEC.md §3a (proxy pattern). Sentinel hostnames
# ('not-yet-deployed.invalid', 'localhost') are filtered out by the
# proxy and treated as "auth not configured" — keeps half-deployed
# states from hitting the broken host.
MOBIUS_OS_AUTH_URL=https://mobius-user-ortabkknqa-uc.a.run.app
CHAT_AUTH_MODE=optional

# Dev-only: enable /chat/admin/mint-dev-token so bench harnesses and
# local frontends can exercise the authed path without a running
# mobius-os service. MUST be 0 in prod. Returns 404 when disabled.
MOBIUS_DEV_TOKEN_ENABLED=1
# TTL of minted dev tokens (seconds). Capped at 1 day in code.
MOBIUS_DEV_TOKEN_TTL_SECONDS=3600

# ── Model profile (Sprint 2 #0, 2026-04-24) ─────────────────────────
# Per-stage model pinning runtime switch. See
# config/model_profiles.yaml for profile definitions and
# app/services/model_profile.py for resolution semantics.
#
# MOBIUS_MODEL_PROFILE picks the startup profile:
#   auto / default / bandit  — Thompson sampling fully in charge (CAN pick Groq)
#   optimal                  — Gemini+Anthropic mix, EXCLUDES Groq (demo default)
#   gemini                   — Vertex only
#   anthropic                — Anthropic only (Sonnet integrator — costlier)
# 2026-04-27: pinned to ``optimal`` after the Groq daily-TPD limit hit
# during quality-bench testing. Profile pins on react_2 to gemini-2.5-flash
# (instead of bandit-picked llama-3.3-70b) so Groq quota exhaustion can't
# kill turns. Per-instance runtime override via POST
# /chat/admin/model-profile still works for ad-hoc switches, but until
# model_profile travels in the chat request payload that override is
# fragile across autoscale (only the instances you POST to honor it).
MOBIUS_MODEL_PROFILE=anthropic
# Admin surface for model-profile endpoints. Defaults to mirroring
# MOBIUS_DEV_TOKEN_ENABLED when unset. Set explicitly to decouple.
MOBIUS_ADMIN_ENABLED=1

# ── Tracing (Sprint 1 #11, 2026-04-24) ───────────────────────────────
# TEMPORARILY DISABLED (2026-04-24): first deploy with tracing on
# (rev40 + rev41) smoked red — POST /chat went from ~0.2s to ~7.5s
# per request. Auto-instrumentation was already off, so the overhead
# is coming from the manual-span path or from OTel's
# TracerProvider/CloudTraceSpanExporter init. Shipping the CODE so
# turning it on is one env flip, but leaving the flag OFF in dev
# until root-caused. See tracing_config.py header for status.
CHAT_TRACE_ENABLED=0
# Fraction of traces to export [0.0, 1.0]. 1.0 = all turns. Drop to
# 0.1 in high-traffic prod.
TRACE_SAMPLE_RATIO=1.0
# Service name as it appears in Cloud Trace. Keep aligned with the
# Cloud Run service name for cross-filtering.
OTEL_SERVICE_NAME=mobius-chat
# Exporter choice. Empty = Cloud Trace (hosted default). "console" =
# dump spans to stdout instead — useful for local-dev debugging.
CHAT_TRACE_EXPORTER=

# ReAct critic — per-round hallucination/fabrication check on LLM
# output. Default OFF in code (awaiting prompt tuning per critic.py
# header comment). Turning on for beta so we exercise the critic
# rounds and promoted task-manager signals (critic_flagged, etc.)
# in real traffic. Flip to 0 if it over-flags.
MOBIUS_REACT_CRITIC=1

# ── Latency hardening (2026-04-22) ──────────────────────────────────
# Per-attempt HTTP timeout for Vertex generate_content. The Vertex
# SDK's internal retry-with-backoff can pile up on 429s — we observed
# 597s elapsed on a single call in dev logs before this cap existed.
# 30s lets the model router's bandit swap to a different model fast
# rather than holding the worker thread hostage.
VERTEX_HTTP_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=30
# Total wall clock for one generate_content call including SDK retries.
# 2026-04-24: the per-attempt timeout alone wasn't enough — the SDK's
# internal retry loop can eat 10 minutes on a 429 storm. Cap total at
# 45s so the bandit can swap models fast when Vertex is throttled.
VERTEX_TOTAL_DEADLINE_SECONDS=45

# Postgres connection pool size per chat instance.
#
# Each chat turn does ~30+ DB ops (thinking_log progress writes,
# retrieval_runs row per corpus_search call, chat_turns at end) plus
# the API thread serves polling /chat/response and history calls in
# parallel. With CHAT_QUEUE_TYPE=redis + min-instances=4 + an
# in-process worker thread per instance, the per-instance burst
# concurrency on the DB pool is roughly:
#   1 worker thread × ~5 conns held briefly through a turn
# + 10 API threads (containerConcurrency) × ~1 conn per request
#
# 2026-04-28: bumped 10 → 20 after silent-worker-hang investigation
# (cid 949df5ea). Pool exhaustion under burst was a plausible cause;
# even when not, 10/instance was undersized for the multi-worker
# fabric. Cloud SQL ``mobius-platform-dev-db`` max_connections is
# ~200 on this tier, so 20/instance × min=4 = 80 baseline / max=20
# instances = 400 ceiling — within bounds for normal traffic, would
# need monitoring if we autoscale broadly.
#
# CHAT_DB_POOL_ACQUIRE_TIMEOUT_S (default 5s, see db_client.py): per-
# acquire deadline. Saturated pool → loud warning + direct-connect
# fallback rather than silent block.
CHAT_DB_POOL_MAX=20

# Post-run adjudicator sampling. Runs on every turn by default (N=1)
# which adds an LLM call worth of Vertex quota per turn for a signal
# we read in aggregate, not per-turn. N=10 = sample ~1/10 turns.
MOBIUS_POST_RUN_ADJUDICATE_EVERY_N=10

# MCP auto-register at startup. Skills MCP is now live at /mcp on the
# provider-roster-credentialing service. Auto-register fetches the tool list
# from CHAT_SKILLS_MCP_URL and adds each tool to the planner manifest on boot.
MOBIUS_MCP_AUTOREGISTER=1

# ── Cache-assist (2026-04-23) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Semantic answer cache fronting RAG. Cached answers from past turns
# show up as a virtual tool result at ReAct round-0 time; the reasoning
# LLM decides whether to use them directly, blend with fresh retrieval,
# or ignore. Reuses the existing CHROMA_HOST wiring — new collection
# ``chat_answer_cache`` alongside ``published_rag``.
#
# 2026-04-27: disabled because cache_assist still uses Chroma at the
# unstable VM (34.170.243.161:8000); UI queries hung at "Cache lookup
# (shadow)..." while the rag service migrated off Chroma. Re-enable
# only after migrating chat_answer_cache to pgvector OR an alternate
# stable store. See conversation log 2026-04-27 for context.
CACHE_ASSIST_ENABLED=0
# Shadow-mode bucket %. 20 pre-launch for aggressive A/B learning;
# drop to 10 after launch. Deterministic on correlation_id so same
# request always lands in the same bucket.
CACHE_ASSIST_BYPASS_PCT=20
# Default max cached answer age in days when the caller doesn't
# specify. Chat's orchestrator passes this as the caller-supplied
# filter profile; specialized agents (strategy/policy) would supply
# their own values. 14 = conservative for healthcare/policy domain.
CACHE_ASSIST_DEFAULT_MAX_AGE_DAYS=14
# Chroma collection name for the answer cache. Separate from
# ``CHROMA_COLLECTION`` (which is the RAG corpus) so the two indexes
# don't interfere.
CACHE_ASSIST_CHROMA_COLLECTION=chat_answer_cache
# Adjudicator quality-score floor for cache-write gate. Turns below
# this score are not written to the cache. 0.0 = write everything
# that passes the other gates; raise if cache quality drifts low.
CACHE_ASSIST_WRITE_QUALITY_FLOOR=0.0

# ── Rate limiting (2026-04-23, Sprint 1 item #6) ────────────────────
# Tiered in-memory limiter. L1 always on when CHAT_RATE_LIMIT_PER_MINUTE
# is set (or when hosted env defaults it). L2 + L3 layer on top —
# first tier to trip returns 429 + Retry-After. In-memory + per-instance;
# with maxScale=5 the effective cap is ~5x looser than configured. Fine
# for beta — migrates to Redis-backed when the queue moves there.
#
# L1 — per-IP. Catches bots + single-client runaway. Active in hosted
# envs by default (30/min if unset).
# Bumped 60→300 on 2026-04-24: a single agentic bench turn polls
# /chat/response/{cid} every 2s for up to 300s = ~150 GETs from one IP.
# 60/min was hitting 429 on legitimate bench + multi-tab demo usage.
# 300/min = ~5 req/s per IP — still catches runaway bots without
# blocking real operator flows.
CHAT_RATE_LIMIT_PER_MINUTE=300
# L2 — per-thread. Soft protection against a frontend retry loop
# doubling-submitting the same thread. 0 = off.
CHAT_RATE_LIMIT_THREAD_PER_MINUTE=20
# L3 — per-user. Stubbed until auth lands — the middleware reads
# ``request.state.user_id`` set by the require_user dependency. When
# CHAT_AUTH_MODE goes to required, this tier activates automatically.
# 0 = off; 120/min is the hosted default when auth is on.
CHAT_RATE_LIMIT_USER_PER_MINUTE=120
# Comma-separated IPs that skip all three tiers. Use sparingly —
# every exemption is a hole. Typical use: internal monitoring / ops
# / the bench harness host.
RATE_LIMIT_EXEMPT_IPS=

# HIPAA posture. Detection-only for beta: every PHI encounter writes
# to phi_audit_log but nothing is blocked. BAA flags stay False until
# Anthropic/Google enterprise contracts are signed.
CHAT_HIPAA_MODE=0
# CHAT_BAA_ANTHROPIC=0
# CHAT_BAA_GOOGLE=0

# ── Cloud Run sizing ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Memory budget is dominated by the Vertex SDK + numpy/chromadb on
# first embedding call (~800 MB). 2 GiB gives headroom for one
# concurrent turn. Increase to 4 GiB before raising CONCURRENCY above 10.
RUN_MEMORY=2Gi
RUN_CPU=2
# Concurrency = in-flight requests per instance. Chat turns are
# LLM-round-trip bound (~3-15s) so low concurrency with many
# instances > high concurrency with few. 10 is a safe starting point.
RUN_CONCURRENCY=10
# Timeout = Cloud Run's hard kill. Must be > MOBIUS_TURN_DEADLINE_S
# so the per-request deadline fires first and returns a useful error
# instead of a connection reset. 360s comfortably exceeds the 300s
# turn deadline (5 min) needed for 10-round agentic turns + 60s of
# Cloud Run draining headroom.
RUN_TIMEOUT=360
# min/max instances. Min=1 avoids cold-start latency for the beta.
# Max=20 (bumped from 5 on 2026-04-24) for the "sharing the link with a
# few more people" phase. Cloud Run only spins up instances when
# concurrency on existing ones is saturated, so idle cost is unchanged.
# Active-hour cost at full scale (20 × 2 vCPU × $0.086 + 20 × 2 GiB ×
# $0.009) ≈ $3.80/hr peak — rarely hit at beta traffic. Watch for
# Cloud SQL connection-pool pressure if sustained: we set
# CHAT_DB_POOL_MAX=10/instance so 20 instances = up to 200 pooled
# connections against the shared Cloud SQL (Postgres default is 100).
# If we see "too many connections", halve RUN_MAX_INSTANCES or
# move to PgBouncer. Monitor at ~10-instance sustained usage.
# 2026-04-27: bumped 1 → 4 to give the chat queue 4 parallel workers.
# Each instance runs an in-process worker thread; with CHAT_QUEUE_TYPE=
# redis (above), all instances share one Redis-backed queue + response
# store. Result: 4 turns can run concurrently instead of single-file.
# 2026-04-28: rolled back 4 → 2. Stress test with 4 warm + autoscale to
# 10 surfaced a ~50% failure rate from Vertex SDK retry-bypass under
# concurrent load (see "vertex.generate_content abandoned after 45s —
# SDK retry ignored our cap" warnings). Until that's fixed, more warm
# instances mean more parallel Vertex calls competing for the same
# project quota — counterproductive. With 2 warm, we cover the typical
# beta load (1-2 concurrent users) without the autoscale-driven cold
# starts that doubled failure rates. Bump back when the Vertex retry
# wrapper lands and we have evidence of sustained >2-concurrent demand.
RUN_MIN_INSTANCES=2
RUN_MAX_INSTANCES=20

# VPC connector — needed so Cloud Run can reach private-IP services
# (Memorystore Redis at 10.40.102.67). Provisioned as
# mobius-dev-vpc-connector (READY) in us-central1; mobius-web-scraper
# already uses it. private-ranges-only egress is sufficient — public
# traffic still goes via Cloud Run's normal egress.
RUN_VPC_CONNECTOR=mobius-dev-vpc-connector
RUN_VPC_EGRESS=private-ranges-only
